    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240\u00b0C/ 220\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 9 then take your<strong> chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chicken-with-soy-honey-butter-pak-choi-and-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Cut 30g <span class=\"text-purple\">[45g]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [60g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> into small pieces</p><p>Cut long rectangles of <strong>tin foil</strong> (approx. the size of A3 sheets of paper), overlap the foil and place on a baking tray (or two!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chicken-with-soy-honey-butter-pak-choi-and-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Place your <strong>chicken </strong>in the centre of the doubled foil (you'll need to 2 rectangles for 4 people) on a baking tray[s]</p><p>Scatter with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> and dot the <strong>butter</strong> evenly over</p><p>Drizzle your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>honey</strong> and <strong>rice vinegar</strong> evenly over the <strong>chicken</strong></p><p>Fold the edges around the foil upwards to enclose the sauce around the chicken</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chicken-with-soy-honey-butter-pak-choi-and-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 17-18 min or until the chicken is cooked through and golden (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>baked chicken with soy honey butter</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chicken-with-soy-honey-butter-pak-choi-and-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the chicken is cooking, wash your <strong>pak choi</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and slice in half lengthways</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chicken-with-soy-honey-butter-pak-choi-and-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>pak choi</strong>, cut-side down, and cook for 2-3 min or until slightly brown</p><p>Once brown, add a splash of<strong> water</strong> and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further or until soft</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chicken-with-soy-honey-butter-pak-choi-and-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>cashews </strong>to a separate baking tray and put them in the oven for 3-4 min or until they have darkened slightly in colour</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Once cooled, chop them coarsely</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/baked-chicken-with-soy-honey-butter-pak-choi-and-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> baked chicken</strong> over the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice</strong>, with the<strong> pak choi</strong> to the side</p><p>Spoon the <strong>soy honey butter</strong> over the <strong>baked chicken</strong> and garnish with the <strong>toasted chopped cashews</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
